Our developers and Chromium team members have had trouble getting the socket API to work due to inadequate documentation.
(See for example issue 434430 and http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11974487/socket-api-not-allowed-in-packaged-apps )

https://developer.chrome.com/apps/manifest/sockets
has an example like this (comments removed for brevity):
{
  &quot;name&quot;: &quot;My Sockets app&quot;,
  &quot;sockets&quot;: {
    &quot;udp&quot;: {
      &quot;send&quot;: &quot;*&quot;
    },
    &quot;tcp&quot;: {
      &quot;connect&quot;: &quot;127.0.0.1:80&quot;
    },
    &quot;tcpServer&quot;: {

      &quot;listen&quot;: &quot;127.0.0.1:80&quot;
    }
  },
  ...
}
...which fails to mention that you have to also have a &quot;permissions&quot; field, as mentioned here:
https://developer.chrome.com/apps/manifest

If you look for more detail on the &quot;permissions&quot; field, you get to:
https://developer.chrome.com/apps/declare_permissions
...which makes it look like you should simply add:
&quot;permissions&quot;: [&quot;socket&quot;]

But in fact, you need to add something more like:
&quot;permissions&quot;: [{&quot;socket&quot;: [&quot;udp-send-to&quot;]}
(I found this eventually at https://github.com/GoogleChrome/chrome-app-samples/blob/master/samples/udp/manifest.json )

I don't know where that's documented, or where it might be documented what values make sense in the list of socket actions. I eventually found it in the code:
https://code.google.com/p/chromium/codesearch#chromium/src/extensions/common/permissions/socket_permission_data.h&amp;l=29

Can we please improve the documentation for this? In particular, I think the socket permissions page needs the most help:
https://developer.chrome.com/apps/manifest/sockets

